{"doc_id": "P18-1034", "doc_idx": 41, "aspect": "challenge", "num_sentences": 32, "pred_indices": [2, 12, 13, 28], "gold_indices": [2, 12], "precision": 0.5, "recall": 1.0, "f1": 0.6666666666666666, "rouge1_model": 0.2702702702702703, "rouge2_model": 0.15068493150684933, "rougeL_model": 0.22972972972972971, "rouge1_oracle": 0.52, "rouge2_oracle": 0.4583333333333333, "rougeL_oracle": 0.52, "oracle_gap_rougeL": 0.2902702702702703, "oracle_indices": [12], "raw_response": "26: Results show that STAMP achieves the new state-of-the-art performance on WikiSQL .\nSentence 27: We conduct extensive experiment analysis to show advantages and limitations of our approach , and where is the room for others to make further improvements .\nSentence 28: SQL language has more complicated queries than the cases included in the WikiSQL dataset , including ( 1 ) querying over multiple relational databases , ( 2 ) nested SQL query as condition value , ( 3 ) more operations such as \" group by \" and \" order by \" , etc .\nSentence 29: In this work , the STAMP model is not designed for the first and second cases , but it could be easily adapted to the third case through incorporating additional SQL keywords and of course the learning of which requires dataset of the same type .\nSentence 30: In the future , we plan to improve the accuracy of the column prediction component .\nSentence 31: We also plan to build a large-scale dataset that considers more sophisticated SQL queries .\nSentence 32: We also plan to extend the approach to low-resource scenarios ( Feng et al . , 2018 ) .\n\nInstructions:\n1. For each sentence, think step-by-step (internally):\n   a. Identify the key claim or information the sentence conveys.\n   b. Map it to one of the three aspects (challenge / approach / outcome).\n   c. Conclude whether it matches \"challenge\": Yes or No.\n2. Select the sentences concluded Yes.\nDo not include the reasoning in the final output.\n\nRules:\n- Select AT MOST 4 sentences for the 