{"doc_id": "2022.naacl-main.46", "doc_idx": 49, "aspect": "challenge", "num_sentences": 34, "pred_indices": [9, 10, 12, 16], "gold_indices": [10, 16], "precision": 0.5, "recall": 1.0, "f1": 0.6666666666666666, "rouge1_model": 0.26923076923076916, "rouge2_model": 0.14285714285714285, "rougeL_model": 0.20512820512820512, "rouge1_oracle": 0.5454545454545454, "rouge2_oracle": 0.30188679245283023, "rougeL_oracle": 0.4727272727272728, "oracle_gap_rougeL": 0.26759906759906765, "oracle_indices": [16], "raw_response": " work ( \u00a7 2 ) as well as relevant Arabic linguistic facts ( \u00a7 3 ) .\nSentence 29: We then define the gender rewriting task in \u00a7 4 and describe the data we use and the gender rewriting model we build in \u00a7 5 and \u00a7 6 .\nSentence 30: Lastly , we present our experimental setup ( \u00a7 7 ) and results ( \u00a7 8) and conclude in \u00a7 9 .\nSentence 31: We defined the task of gender rewriting in contexts involving two users ( I and/or You ) , and developed a multi-step system that combines the positive aspects of both rule-based and neural rewriting models .\nSentence 32: Our best models establish the benchmark for this newly defined task and the SOTA for a previously defined first person version of it .\nSentence 33: We further demonstrated a use case of our gender rewriting system by post-editing the output of a commercial MT system to provide personalized outputs based on the users ' grammatical gender preferences .\nSentence 34: In future work , we plan to explore the use of other pretrained models , and to work on the problem of gender rewriting in other languages and dialectal varieties .\n\nInstructions:\n1. For each sentence, think step-by-step (internally):\n   a. Identify the key claim or information the sentence conveys.\n   b. Map it to one of the three aspects (challenge / approach / outcome).\n   c. Conclude whether it matches \"challenge\": Yes or No.\n2. Select the sentences concluded Yes.\nDo not include the reasoning in the final output.\n\nRules:\n- Select AT MOST 4 sentences for the \"challenge\" aspect.\n- If no sentences match, return an empty list.\n- Indices are 1-based.\n- Return ONLY valid JSON.\n\nReturn format:\n{\"selected_sentences\": [list_of_sentence_numbers]}\nmodel\nthought\n```json\n{\"selected_sentences\": [9, 10, 12, 16]}\n```////////////////</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>/</b>"}
